com.google.android.exoplayer2.ext.mediasession

Class MediaSessionConnector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.android.exoplayer2.ext.mediasession.MediaSessionConnector

  • public final class MediaSessionConnector
extends java.lang.Object
    Connects a MediaSessionCompat to a Player.

    The connector listens for actions sent by the media session's controller and implements these actions by calling appropriate player methods. The playback state of the media session is automatically synced with the player. The connector can also be optionally extended by providing various collaborators:

    • Actions to initiate media playback (PlaybackStateCompat#ACTION_PREPARE_* and PlaybackStateCompat#ACTION_PLAY_*) can be handled by a MediaSessionConnector.PlaybackPreparer passed when calling setPlayer(Player, PlaybackPreparer, CustomActionProvider...). Custom actions can be handled by passing one or more MediaSessionConnector.CustomActionProviders in a similar way.
    • To enable a media queue and navigation within it, you can set a MediaSessionConnector.QueueNavigator by calling setQueueNavigator(QueueNavigator). Use of TimelineQueueNavigator is recommended for most use cases.
    • To enable editing of the media queue, you can set a MediaSessionConnector.QueueEditor by calling setQueueEditor(QueueEditor).
    • An ErrorMessageProvider for providing human readable error messages and corresponding error codes can be set by calling setErrorMessageProvider(ErrorMessageProvider).

        Parameters:

      • MediaSessionConnector

        public MediaSessionConnector(android.support.v4.media.session.MediaSessionCompat mediaSession,
                             MediaSessionConnector.PlaybackController playbackController,
                             boolean doMaintainMetadata,
                             @Nullable
                             java.lang.String metadataExtrasPrefix)
        Creates an instance. Must be called on the same thread that is used to construct the player instances passed to setPlayer(Player, PlaybackPreparer, CustomActionProvider...).
        Parameters:
        mediaSession - The MediaSessionCompat to connect to.
        playbackController - A MediaSessionConnector.PlaybackController for handling playback actions, or null if the connector should handle playback actions directly.
        doMaintainMetadata - Whether the connector should maintain the metadata of the session. If false, you need to maintain the metadata of the media session yourself (provide at least the duration to allow clients to show a progress bar).
        metadataExtrasPrefix - A string to prefix extra keys which are propagated from the active queue item to the session metadata.

      • setPlayer

        public void setPlayer(Player player,
                      MediaSessionConnector.PlaybackPreparer playbackPreparer,
                      MediaSessionConnector.CustomActionProvider... customActionProviders)
        Sets the player to be connected to the media session.

        The order in which any MediaSessionConnector.CustomActionProviders are passed determines the order of the actions published with the playback state of the session.

        Parameters:
        player - The player to be connected to the MediaSession.
        playbackPreparer - An optional MediaSessionConnector.PlaybackPreparer for preparing the player.
        customActionProviders - An optional MediaSessionConnector.CustomActionProviders to publish and handle custom actions.
